articles.author: Jihye Lee, Lim Hui Jie
articles.title: Asia-Pacific markets largely higher ahead of Australia's interest rate decision - CNBC
articles.description: Asian markets are higher after the RBA hiked rates by 25 points, surprising traders.
articles.content:
In a surprise move, the Reserve Bank of Australia raised its cash rate target by 25 basis points to 3.85%, stating that inflation in the nation is "still too high."
